The paper deals with lower bounds for well-studied #P-hard problems, which are related to computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as likely sub-categories. The Tutte polynomial is a topic in algebraic graph theory, which could place the paper in cs.CG (Computational Geometry) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as well.
